pwnsjp (0.8.1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Update versions and dates in README, TODO, and in the configure script.
  * Fix a few type mismatches on 64-bit architectures.
  * Don't require non-standard <endian.h> and <byteswap.h> headers.
  * Improve the build system:
    + Use pkg-config to determine ncursesw location.
    + Fall back to default compiler flags if pkg-config data for zlib or
      ncursesw cannot be found.
    + Strip trailing slash from the --with-dictdir argument.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Wed, 12 Jun 2013 16:40:03 +0200

pwnsjp (0.8) unstable; urgency=low

  * Change version numbering scheme.
  * Fix incorrect rendering of quotation marks.
  * Rephrase some error messages.
  * Remove the “AUTHOR” section from the manual pages, as per man-pages(7)
    recommendation.
  * Fix “make distclean” to remove also files generated by make, not only
    those generated by configure.
  * Drop Intel C++ Compiler compatibility code.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Thu, 07 Feb 2013 21:28:32 +0100

pwnsjp (0.700) unstable; urgency=low

  * Document the -f/--file options.
  * Prefer U+2018 LEFT SINGLE QUOTATION MARK to U+201B SINGLE HIGH-REVERSED-9
    QUOTATION MARK.
  * Use Autoconf.
  * Relicense to the Expat license.
  * Remove Debian packaging from the tarball.
  * Remove some unused code.
  * Rewrite README (in English).

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Wed, 11 Jul 2012 21:08:30 +0200

